    "large cumulative expected revenue losses caused by offering suboptimal assortments.",
    "Hence, the question is how much time should be spent in learning customer preferences before exploiting the best assortment determined till then.",
    "This problem is referred to as exploration-exploitation trade-off and is characteristic for this type of dynamic assortment problem, see Caro and Gallien (2007).",
    "The overall goal in such dynamic settings is to minimize the cumulative regret or to maximize the expected cumulative revenue over the whole selling horizon, see e.g.",
    "Rusmevichientong et al. (2010) and Bernstein et al. (2019)."
